HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 692
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor Craig Norris upon the occasion of his
retirement from the Tennessee Wildlife
Resources Agency.
WHEREAS, Wildlife Officer Craig Norris is taking a much-deserved retirement from the
Tennessee Wildlife Resources Agency (TWRA) after dedicating thirty-five years of service to the
State of Tennessee, primarily in Pickett County; and
WHEREAS, Officer Norris's organizational skills and knowledge of Pickett County
provided great support for the county's residents and the agency mission he served; and
WHEREAS, after serving his first two years as a wildlife officer in Van Buren County,
Craig Norris transferred to Pickett County, where he remained for the rest of his career and
became an integral part of the community; and
WHEREAS, noted for his dedication to the community's needs and priorities, Officer
Norris always served with his heart, whether he was educating hunters, enforcing boating safety
laws on Dale Hollow Reservoir, conducting school programs, or connecting with hunters and
anglers; and
WHEREAS, he particularly enjoyed working the walleye run on the East Fork of the
Obey River and interacting with his fellow officers; and
WHEREAS, his TWRA commanding officer praised Mr. Norris as "a steady hand and a
great community officer" who approached "even the most stressful situations with a calmness,
experience, and knowledge"; and
WHEREAS, Craig Norris grew up in Overton County, hunting and fishing with his dad;
his childhood dream was to become a game warden; and
